      "note_no": "33",
      "note": "As regards the tribe of Ad, the above seems to be an allusion to their one-time capital, the legendary \"Iram the many-pillared\" (mentioned in the Qur'an only once, namely, in 89:7). It has since been buried by the moving sand-dunes of Al-Ahqaf (a region between 'Uman and Hadramawt, within the great South-Arabian desert of Rub' al-Khali); it is said, however, that its traces are occasionally uncovered by strong winds. For an explanation of the reference to the dwellings of the Thamud, see note 59 on 7:74."
